data<-read.csv("creditcard.csv")
#View(credit_data)
data$Class <- as.factor(data$Class)
data %>% 
  group_by(Class) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=Class, y=V1, fill=Class)) +
  geom_boxplot() 

data %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=V2, fill=Class)) +
  geom_density(alpha=0.8, color='black') +
  ggtitle('Density Plot') 

set.seed(1234)
ind <- sample(2,nrow(data),replace=TRUE, prob=c(0.8,.2))
train <- data[ind==1,]
test <- data[ind==2,]
# Naive Bayes
model <- naive_bayes(Class ~ ., data = train)
model

# Predict
p <- predict(model, data, type= 'class')
## Warning: predict.naive_bayes(): more features in the newdata are provided as

table_mat
